article.headline: Weber State beats Montana State 65-62
article.story: OGDEN, Utah -- Joel Bolomboy posted a double-double, scoring 17 points with 11 rebounds as Weber State beat Montana State 65-62 on Saturday night. Jeremy Senglin added 15 points and Richaud Gittens had 14 for the Wildcats (7-8, 2-2 Big Sky), who shot 36.7 percent from the field overall and 77.4 percent from the line. The Bobcats (3-13, 0-4) went 16-8 to start the first period before a Chris Golden 3-pointer sparked a 10-0 run to help Weber State build a 32-29 halftime lead. Montana State opened the second half with a 13-3 run, featuring a pair of 3s by Danny Robinson and another by Michael Dison to take a 42-35 lead with 15:10 remaining. But the Wildcats clawed back to take a 57-51 lead on a Gittens 3-pointer with 4:50 left and held on for the win. Dison led Montana State with 17 points, five rebounds and five steals.
